snippet.textDisplay: This is , outcome of Ganga -Jamuni tehjeeb which developed in Oudhi(a princely state in UP  ruled by muslims).The subedar of of Oudh established his own state from Mughals after the Aurranjeb. Art culture, music, dance flourished under thier rule. These rulers liked the the local culture and refined and polished local dance, music, embroidery. The new culture developed in Oudh is called Ganga -Jamuni tehjeeb, hindu-muslim because ganga n Jamuna Rivers are merge in the Oudh area. Kathak dance was also developed here. Poetry in Oudhi was in its peak. Famous song Babul mora naihar chhuto  jaye which is famous song of bollywood movie sung by KL Sehgal, was written by Wajid Ali Shah, last nawab. It was written by him when he was made captive by Britishers n forcely taken out of Lucknow to put him prison in Calcutta. Urdu language was also developed here.
